==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# the act of [[receiving]], or the fact of having been [[received]]
#(''in plural'') a [[quantity]] or [[amount]] received; [[takings]]
# a [[written]] [[acknowledgment]] that a [[specified]] [[article]] or [[sum]] of [[money]] has been received
# a [[recipe]]

===Verb===
'''to receipt'''  {{transitive}} or {{intransitive}}

# to [[give]] or [[write]] a receipt (for something)
# to [[mark]] a [[bill]] as having been [[paid]]

===Related terms===
*[[receive]]

===Translations===
;Act of receiving
*French: [[réception]]
*Malagasy: [[ray]]
;Written acknowledgment
*French: for money or for hand-given thing: [[reçu]], [[récépissé]]; for owed money: any of the preceding or [[quittance]] (specially for rents); for sent e-mail, letter, parcel: [[accusé]] de [[réception]]

